2️⃣ ACADEMIC YEAR MANAGEMENT
This is structurally critical.
Data Model
institutes/{id}/academicYears/{yearId}
{
  startDate,
  endDate,
  status: "Active | Locked | Archived",
  archivedAt,
  snapshotId
}

2.1 View Current Year
Display:
    • Academic Year Label
    • Status Badge:
        ◦ 🟢 Active
        ◦ 🟡 Locked
        ◦ ⚫ Archived
    • Student Count
    • Run Count
    • Snapshot status

2.2 Lock Academic Year
Effect:
    • Prevent new test generation under this year
    • Prevent new assignments
    • Freeze studentYearMetrics
    • Disable execution mode toggles
Allowed only if:
noActiveAttempts == true
Lock action logs audit event.

2.3 Archive Academic Year (HIGH-RISK ACTION)
Irreversible.
Double confirmation required:
    1. Confirm no active tests
    2. Confirm archive action
Trigger sequence:
1. Generate final governance snapshot
2. Seal studentYearMetrics
3. Export session data to BigQuery
4. Move Firestore HOT collections to WARM partition
5. Clear HOT session collections
6. Initialize new academic year
After archive:
    • Year becomes read-only
    • Appears in Governance longitudinal comparison
    • No recalculation allowed

3️⃣ DEFAULT EXECUTION POLICIES
This controls structural behavior — not performance history.

3.1 Phase Defaults
L0 / L1
Admin can set:
    • Phase 1 %
    • Phase 2 %
    • Phase 3 %
Validation:
Must sum to 100%.
Stored as:
executionDefaults.phaseSplit

L2+
Additional Controls:
    • Enable Adaptive Phase Engine (default ON)
    • Allow Manual Override? (Boolean)
    • Hard Mode Availability (license dependent)
Manual override must not break test integrity.

3.2 Timing Policy (L2+ Only)
Define preset timing windows per difficulty.
Example schema:
timingPresets: {
  "JEE_MAIN": {
      easy: { min: 30, max: 60 },
      medium: { min: 60, max: 150 },
      hard: { min: 150, max: 210 }
  }
}
Guardrails:
    • No per-question arbitrary timing edits
    • Reset to system defaults option available

3.3 Alert Frequency Policy (L1+)
Admin controls:
    • Alert cooldown interval
    • Max alerts per test section
    • Escalation threshold
Purpose:
Prevent alert fatigue.
Stored separately from Insights logic.

